	<Title>
		No time for exercise? No way!
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;If it&apos;s hard to find time for exercise, don&apos;t fall back on excuses. Schedule workouts as you would any other important activity. You can also slip in physical activity throughout the day. Be creative! Take a walk during your child&apos;s music lesson. Take the stairs instead of the elevator at work. Pedal a stationary bike or do strength training exercises with resistance tubing while you watch TV at night.&lt;/p&gt;
